Certainly! Here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "jadan" in different forms and positions:

1. Jadan sam danas. (*jadan*) (I'm miserable today.)
2. Nemoj da se smeješ njemu, jadan je. (*jadan*) (Don't laugh at him, he's pitiful.)
3. Što sam jadan kad sam sam. (jadan) (How wretched I am when I'm alone.)
4. Videla sam ga kako jadno plače. (*jadno*) (I saw him crying miserably.)
5. Jadan pas nije imao šta da jede. (*jadan*) (The poor dog had nothing to eat.)
6. To je bilo jadno gledati. (*jadno*) (It was pitiful to watch.)
7. Jadan je život bez ljubavi. (*jadan*) (Life is wretched without love.)
8. Dajte mu malo jadne hrane. (*jadne*) (Give him some meager food.)

I hope these examples are helpful!